  "riddle": "1. Unearth the story of a Puerto Rican politician who began his journey in 1979. What date graced his entrance into the world?\n\n2. Journey to the land down under and investigate the varieties of local governance. How many distinct types are categorized in their local administrative systems?\n\n3. Seek the representatives tasked with federal governance in Australia. Discover how many electorates exist in their House of Representatives.\n\n4. Dive into the geography of these electorates; what is their height above sea level?\n\n5. Nearby this political hub, how many establishments serving meals can you find?\n\n6. Combine the elevation you discovered in clue 4 with the number of eateries from clue 5 for a total to report back.\n\n7. Navigate to India and uncover the governmental structure that governs its cities. How many languages interconnect in the interlanguage links of this municipal page?\n\n8. Reflect on the number from your last clue; what is the sum of its digits?\n\n9. Turn your attention to a member of the legislative body who serves a nation. How many languages are listed at the top of their article?\n\n10. In a mountainous state, find the office holder known for leading the executive branch. What is the term length assigned to their role in years?\n\n11. Ascend to the altitude of this political position. What is the elevation, measured above sea level?\n\n12. Counting the sacred spots nearby this office, how many temples stand within reach?\n\n13. Weave together the elevation from clue 11 and the temple count from clue 12 to find the absolute difference between these two figures.\n\n14. Ascertain the height once more above sea level for this executive office.\n\n15. Engage with the number of years they serve in office from clue 10. How many ways can you divide that number evenly?\n\n16. Calculate the days that separate July 29, 1949, from March 16, 2026. What is the total?\n\n17. Finally, compute the digital root of the total from clue 3 added to the even distribution count from clue 15. As you unravel this mystery, remember that your answer should be a single digit from 0 to 9!",
